Sentencas: A highly stable electrode based on La0.6Sr0.4Co3-delta (LSC) was developed for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: A La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-based electrode wit high durability for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode was prepared by impregnating LSC into a porous samaria-doped ceria (SDC, Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9) frame, which was deposited to an SDC electrolyte using screen-printing and co-firing techniques.
Titulo: A La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-based electrode wit high durability for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of the composite electrode were investigated by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: A La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-based electrode wit high durability for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: High stability upon thermal cycle was demonstrated for this composite electrode although LSC and SDC have significant difference in thermal expansion.
Titulo: A La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-based electrode wit high durability for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After 20 times of 500-800 degrees C thermal cycles and 10 times of room-temperature-to- 800 degrees C thermal cycles, no increase in area specific resistance (ASR) was observed for such electrodes.
Titulo: A La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-based electrode wit high durability for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, improved performance was achieved with the impregnated composite electrode when compared with a conventional composite electrode prepared with a screen-printing technique.
Titulo: A La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-based electrode wit high durability for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
